The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Moya to play in Chennai Open

Chennai: Former world number one and defending champion Carlos Moya of Spain, who has 18 ATP singles championships under his belt, has pitched himself to score a hattrick of title wins in the Chennai Open starting here on January 2. 

The Spaniard, who had won South Asias only ATP championship twice in a row (2003 and 2004), has confirmed participation. 

The tournament is great and the enthusiasm of the crowds is very encouraging. I love India and it is always a pleasure to come back here, Moya said. 

This is the fourth time that I will play here, and having won the title I am confident that I will be able to raise my game to the highest level and get a great start once again to the new ATP champions race, he said in a press release by the owners of the championship. (PTI) 




